description:
&lt;p&gt;The Royal Free Hospital’s Emergency Department is looking for emergency department assistants to come and work with the established team. You should be enthusiastic and dynamic and enjoy working in a busy environment. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Applicants should have previous experience of working in a health care setting ideally with a qualification. The successful candidate will be supported in this role by the A&amp;E team with opportunities for further educational advancement available due to our development programmes and strong links with Middlesex universities.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Previous post holders have successfully entered nursing and medical training programmes. There are a wide variety of opportunities for development. The department is undergoing an extensive redevelopment transforming us into up to date World Class Care facility. Come and join us at this very exciting time&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Please see person specification for details of required experience and qualifications. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Our Emergency Department sees over 90,000 patients a year, and has an integrated Paediatric Emergency Department and an Urgent Care Centre. In addition to this, we are in the unique position of having a consultant led care of the Elderly Team who assess older patients for appropriate admission or organise enhanced social care support in the community. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Urgent Care Centre within our Emergency Department has our ENPs working with the GPs to deliver an efficient and responsive service.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Deepa Earnest - &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Matron – Emergency Department - 0207 794 0500 Ext 39837&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
